				<span class="postdetails">
					<br /><b>Joined:</b> Sun Apr 13, 2008 11:12 am<br /><b>Posts:</b> 7391<br /><b>Location:</b> Seattle
				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The actual literal contents of the ROM control whether the cart can address two 1 MiB ROMs or one 2 MiB ROM.<br /><br />MMX2, 1.5MiB, always was on 2 ROMs.<br />MMX3, 2 MiB, was always on 1 ROM.<br /><br />The program data in MMX3 configures the CX4 to address one 2 MiB ROM. The data in MMX2 configures the CX4 to address two 1 MiB ROMs.<br /><br />On the 2DC0N board, the left one (labeled U1) is the &quot;first&quot; one. Both ROMs are connected completely in parallel, EXCEPT that they each have their own chip enable pin.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

